# AFL Tipping App

Welcome to the AFL Tipping App! This is a React application built using the `create-react-app` package to help you manage and enjoy your family's AFL Tipping. With this app, you can easily create, join, and participate in friendly AFL Tippings within your family and friends.

## Getting Started

To get started with the AFL Tipping App, follow these steps:

### Prerequisites

Make sure you have the following software installed on your machine:

- Node.js: You'll need Node.js to run the development server and manage dependencies. You can download it from the official website: [Node.js](https://nodejs.org/)

### Installation

1. Clone this repository to your local machine:

   ```bash
   git clone https://github.com/rubyw222/tipsters.git
   ```

2. Navigate to the project directory:

   ```bash
   cd tipsters
   ```

3. Install the project dependencies:

   ```bash
   npm install
   ```

### Running the Development Server

1. Start the development server:

   ```bash
   npm start
   ```

2. Open your web browser and navigate to [http://localhost:3000](http://localhost:3000) to view the app.

### Usage

TBC

### Features (still in build)

- User authentication and account management
- Create and manage tipping competitions
- Join existing competitions using unique codes
- Make weekly match predictions and submit tips
- Leaderboard to track competition standings

## Project Structure

The project structure follows the conventions set by `create-react-app`. Here's an overview of the main directories and files:

- `src/`: Contains the application source code
  - `assets/`: Static assets like images and styles
  - `App.js`: Main application component
  - `index.js`: Entry point of the application
- `public/`: Static assets that are publicly accessible
- `README.md`: Project documentation (you're reading it!)

